      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ICE QUEEN (11) broke last start and finished 30 metres from the winner in fourth over 1609m at Port Pirie unfortunate start to this prep. No favours expected from this draw. Won't find this any harder so she can return to form. CECIL PEAK (3) finished third last start, beaten 9 metres at this track over 1800m. Expecting a very good run. CHIARA MARA (8) is stepping out for the first time. By Mel Mara and hails from the J K Neilson, K Wilson stable. Can travel in a nice spot from this draw and wait on the sprint lane if necessary. Was not far away in a recent trial. Has the right credentials to play a major role. THE MAJOR DANGER (4) is the best of the rest after finishing third when resuming over 1800m at this track last time out.",
